&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Paediatric Nurse to join the team in Children’s Assessment Unit / Paediatric Emergency Department, at Dewsbury and District Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be a permanent post, with rotation across site at Pinderfields Hospital and also supporting other Paediatric Departments in the Trust. We are looking for ideally an experienced Paediatric Nurse, who is confident in working both areas - Children’s Assessment and Children’s Emergency Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department provides 24 hour care in Emergency Department and the assessment is open for 12 hours in the day; this will require a 24 hour working pattern covering nights and days across site, with the additional shift of 09:30 – 22:00 when working on Children’s Assessment unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We desire someone who is hard working, enthusiastic, dedicated and has a passion for delivering quality paediatric care. We are a friendly and supportive team rising to the challenges and working hard to achieve our targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you require any further information, please contact Katharine Bickerdyke on k.bickerdyke@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
